<doc id="1181571" wikidata="Q112237" url="?curid=1181571" title="Zone, Lombardy">
<text>Zone (Brescian: ) is a &quot;comune&quot; in the province of Brescia, in Lombardy, northern Italy. It is situated in a mountain valley east of Lake Iseo. The town is known for the nearby &quot;Pyramids of Zone&quot;, formations of large rock pillars created by erosion. Its coat of arms shows three of these pillars.

