<doc id="1181626" wikidata="Q4391123" url="?curid=1181626" title="Sikkim Janata Congress">
<text>Sikkim Janata Congress (translation: &quot;Sikkim Popular Congress&quot;) was a political party in Sikkim, active in the struggle for democratic reforms. SJC was founded when the Sikkim State Congress and Sikkim Janata Party merged, in October 1972. K.C.Pradhan was its president.

In 1973, SJC merged with Dorjee&#x27;s Sikkim National Congress.

